 false, "score": 74, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8650078, "raw_content": "President Donald Trump rescinded two executive orders Friday from the 1970s that had governed off-road vehicle use on federal public lands, directing agencies to dismantle a regulatory framework he called vague, burdensome, and an obstacle to legitimate access.\r\n\r\nThe order revokes Executive Order 11644 and Executive Order 11989, which together required agency leaders to manage off-road vehicle use on public lands under a set of subjective criteria\u2014including preventing adverse effects on natural, aesthetic, or scenic values and minimizing conflicts between off-road vehicles and other existing or proposed recreational uses.", "author": "Bullet3250", "created": 1780193012670, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Marat1792", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Trump Rescinds 50-Year-Old Rules Banning Off-Road Vehicles on Federal Lands", "last_comment_created": 1780198908406, "content": "<p>President Donald Trump rescinded two executive orders Friday from the 1970s that had governed off-road vehicle use on federal public lands, directing agencies to dismantle a regulatory framework he called vague, burdensome, and an obstacle to legitimate access.</p>\n<p>The order revokes Executive Order 11644 and Executive Order 11989, which together required agency leaders to manage off-road vehicle use on public lands under a set of subjective criteria\u2014including preventing adverse effects on natural, aesthetic, or scenic values and minimizing conflicts between off-road vehicles and other existing or proposed recreational uses.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier"